In accordance with subsection (b)(1) and (2) of this section, the services to be provided for seriously emotionally disturbed individuals or autistic children may include, but are not limited to:
Respite services;
Family training and education;
Day treatment services;
Therapeutic integration services;
Intensive individual support services;
Therapeutic living services;
Intensive in-home intervention services; and
Specialized case management services.
